16 (2) "Base year" means the taxable year immediately preceding the taxable year in which
17 the exemption under subsection (b) of this section is first granted to the most recent
18 owner of such homestead.
19 (3) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
20 the O.C.G.A., as amended, with the additional qualification that it shall include not more
21 than one-half contiguous acres of homestead property.
22 (4) "Senior citizen" means a person who is 67 years of age or older on or before
23 January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption under subsection (c) of this
24 section is made.
25 (b) Each resident of the Oglethorpe County school district who is a senior citizen is granted
26 an exemption on such person's homestead from Oglethorpe County school district ad valorem
27 taxes for educational purposes in an amount equal to the amount by which the current year
28 assessed value of such homestead exceeds the base year assessed value, including any final
29 determination of value on appeal pursuant to Code Section 48-5-311 of the O.C.G.A., as
30 amended, of such homestead. This exemption shall not apply to taxes assessed on
31 improvements to such homestead or additional land that is added to such homestead after
32 January 1 of the base year. If any real property is removed from such homestead, the base
33 year assessed value, including any final determination of value on appeal pursuant to Code
34 Section 48-5-311 of the O.C.G.A., as amended, shall be adjusted to reflect such removal, and
35 the exemption shall be recalculated accordingly. The value of that property in excess of such
36 exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
37 (c) A person shall not receive the homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this
38 section unless such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner
39 of Oglethorpe County, giving such information relative to receiving such exemption as will
40 enable the tax commissioner of Oglethorpe County to make a determination regarding the
41 initial and continuing eligibility of such person for such exemption. The tax commissioner
42 of Oglethorpe County shall provide application forms for this purpose.
